The change was necessary to accommodate all Old Males and Old Girls from all schools in the South Island. All Old Boys in the South Island had been members of the Old Boys Club, but it was dissolved when only Old Boys from the main Old Boys clubs in the North Island (King's and Chiltonians) submitted applications to start new Old Boys' Club in the South Island.[1]

Barefoot club

In 2008, Tonga National Rugby League (TNRFL) made a play for the top spot in the Omnium Pacifico Series by pledging to pay all expenses if four selected players played on the same team in a Tri-Nations Tournament called the 2008 Tri-Nations Tournament or Pentathlon. Other competitors included champions Australia, New Zealand and Samoa. The players were offered the opportunity according to a list published by the TNRFL chairman.[4] According to the TNL president, Viliami Mafile'A,[5] The prize was worth $10,000 in reality, which was enough for one player. Other players excluded were American Samoa, Cook Islands, France, Fiji, Hong Kong, Korea, New Caledonia, Niue, North America, Papua New Guinea, Romania, Russia, Solomon Islands, Thailand and Timor Leste.
